<span id="freeTextContainer14265117346239495063">What a great follow up to the first in the series, <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6294.Howl_s_Moving_Castle__Howl_s_Moving_Castle___1_' title='Howl&apos;s Moving Castle (Howl&apos;s Moving Castle, #1) by Diana Wynne Jones' rel='nofollow noopener'>Howl&apos;s Moving Castle</a>! <br/><br/>This isn&apos;t a typical series in that the main characters from the first book don&apos;t appear in the second book until about 2/3 of the way through. But the humor and the whimsical magic and great characters are still very much here. I also enjoy the way animals play a significant role in her stories. They make the most interesting characters!<br/><br/>I&apos;m thoroughly enjoying becoming reacquainted with DWJ. She has written so many books, </span>
  <span id="freeText14265117346239495063" style="display:none">What a great follow up to the first in the series, <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6294.Howl_s_Moving_Castle__Howl_s_Moving_Castle___1_" title="Howl's Moving Castle (Howl's Moving Castle, #1) by Diana Wynne Jones" rel="nofollow noopener">Howl's Moving Castle</a>! <br /><br />This isn't a typical series in that the main characters from the first book don't appear in the second book until about 2/3 of the way through. But the humor and the whimsical magic and great characters are still very much here. I also enjoy the way animals play a significant role in her stories. They make the most interesting characters!<br /><br />I'm thoroughly enjoying becoming reacquainted with DWJ. She has written so many books, and I'm grateful for that. Her humor and effortlessly created magical worlds make me feel like a little kid again as I read, and Jenny Sterlin does a magnificent job with the narration of this entire series. <br /><br />2020 just may be a DWJ year for me. No one does humor and magic the way she does. This seems to be my sweet reading spot right now. 💚</span>
  <a data-text-id="14265117346239495063" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

