<span id="freeTextContainer17018305884124482777">I thought this was really fun read, just slightly more than Howl&apos;s Moving Castle, which I was surprised by! The main character in this one, Abdullah, speaks in the most ridiculous, flowery way, and I loved it! I can see why people might get bored of it after a while, but I continued to find it very charming. Probably my main issue was Abdullah equating slimness with beauty, and of course the whole insta-love thing between him and Flower-in-the-Night (what a name...). I was so intrigued to find o</span>
  <span id="freeText17018305884124482777" style="display:none">I thought this was really fun read, just slightly more than Howl's Moving Castle, which I was surprised by! The main character in this one, Abdullah, speaks in the most ridiculous, flowery way, and I loved it! I can see why people might get bored of it after a while, but I continued to find it very charming. Probably my main issue was Abdullah equating slimness with beauty, and of course the whole insta-love thing between him and Flower-in-the-Night (what a name...). I was so intrigued to find out how exactly this is a sequel to Howl's Moving Castle though, and I really liked how that was revealed! <br /><br />Overall I found this a delightfully cute read and I'd say it's a 3.5-4 star from me.</span>
